{"key":"post-9511569","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9511569</id>\n<content>Don't put any sort of digital timer or thermostat inside a high humidity environment such as a fruiting chamber.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you're trying to colonize your jars in a cold area, simply plug in a space heater nearby to take the chill off the air. They all are made with built in thermostats, usually labeled 1-9. Simply tweak it to where it keeps the area at normal room temperature. There is no reason to get anal about trying to maintain 24C to 27C.&amp;nbsp; It's not that important, contrary to lots of 5+ year old posts around here to the contrary.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9511661</next>\n<prev>9511478</prev>\n<first>9511220</first>\n<last>9512052</last>\n<when>1230570149</when>\n<utime>12/29/08 07:02 PM</utime>\n</post>"}